nl_problem:
# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 5)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int, x3: int, x4: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0
4. x3 is greater than 0
5. x4 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ( (x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) (x3 int) (x4 int) ) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "x0 must be greater than 0")
    (constraint "x1 must be greater than 0")
    (constraint "x2 must be greater than 0")
    (constraint "x3 must be greater than 0")
    (constraint "x4 must be greater than 0")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Determine if all input integers are greater than zero, using nested if statements.")
    (rule "The function must return True only if all input integers are greater than zero.")
    (return "Returns True if all input integers are greater than zero. Otherwise, returns False.")
  )
)
